    },
    {
      question: "Why start at £2,000 when I've been quoted a few hundred?",
      answer:
        "Because a £300 website and a £2,000 website aren't the same product at different prices — they're different things. The cheap one is usually a template filled in fast, with no thought to whether it ranks or turns visitors into enquiries. Mine are designed around getting you work and built to last.",
    },
    {
      question: "How long does it take?",
      answer:
        "Most builds run a few weeks from our first call to launch — the variable is usually how quickly content and photos come together, not the build itself. I'll give you an honest timeline up front.",
